<item>
            <title>[SOLR-5667] Performance problem when not using hdfs block cache.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-5667</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Reads are terribly slow due to what looks like a too small buffer in the buffered input. This has consequences for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-1301&quot; title=&quot;Add a Solr contrib that allows for building Solr indexes via Hadoop&amp;#39;s Map-Reduce.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-1301&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-1301&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, as we turn off the block cache when writing indexes with map-reduce.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
