[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1563766&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1563766&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-5667&quot; title=&quot;Performance problem when not using hdfs block cache.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-5667&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-5667&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Performance problem when not using hdfs block cache.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13889203" author="jira-bot" created="Mon, 3 Feb 2014 04:12:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1563770 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=markrmiller%40gmail.com&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;markrmiller@gmail.com&quot;&gt;markrmiller@gmail.com&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;dev/branches/branch_4x&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1563770&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1563770&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-5667&quot; title=&quot;Performance problem when not using hdfs block cache.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-5667&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-5667&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Performance problem when not using hdfs block cache.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13890997" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Tue, 4 Feb 2014 18:49:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I put in a 32k buffer for now. Other parts in the code use a 32k buffer already (when the block cache is on), and initial performance testing showed it to performant. It fixes the performance bug.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I do think we want to look at the optimal settings and sizes throughout the hdfs directory and block cache code, but that should be done more holistically rather than as part of this discreet performance bug fix. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
